'''''Psychological Injury and Law''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]] on behalf of the [[Association for Scientific Advancement in Psychological Injury and Law]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ASAPIL website |url=http://www.asapil.net |publisher=Association for Scientific Advancement in Psychological Injury and Law |accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> It was established in 2008 and the [[editor-in-chief]] is Gerald Young ([[York University]]). The journal covers [[forensic psychology]], especially the interaction of [[psychology]] and law in the area of [[Psychological trauma|trauma]] and injury.

== Abstracting and indexing ==
The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[Scopus]], [[PsycINFO]], and [[Academic OneFile]].

